Name: Document Number
Definition: The document number assigned to a patent application on publication. e.g. 20130227762

Name: Patent ID
Definition: A string used to identify a patent. Important to note: this is not always a consistent 'identifier' as such as a combination of jurisdiction, document number, application stage that can be used to identify a patent document. While most patent id formats can be used to uniquely id patents, different datasets might use different formats.

Name: DocDB ID
Definition: The DocDB identifier of a patent document (assigned by EPO worldwide bibliographic data)

Name: Patent Family
Definition: Information pertaining to the patent's family

Name: Publication Date
Definition: Date of publication, for a paper or patent document

Name: PubMed ID
Definition: Identifier associated with biomedical and life sciences journal literature

Name: Lens ID
Definition: Unique lens identifier. Every document in the Lens has a unique 15-digit identifier called a Lens ID. e.g. 186-488-232-022-055

Name: DOI
Definition: Digital Object Identifier, used to uniquely ID academic papers

Name: ISSN
Definition: International Standard Serial Number, used to uniquely id serial publications

Name: ISBN
Definition: International Standard Book Number, used to uniquely identify books

Name: CPC
Definition: The CPC classification indicates the subject to which the patent relates.
